		<index indexName="text" corresp="acs0000153-md.xml"/>
		<body>
			<pb n="81" facs="acs0000001-02-096"/>
			<head rendition="#center #u">Before a Crucifix.</head>
			<lg>
				<l n="1">Here, <subst><del seq="1"><unclear cert="low">wasted</unclear></del><add seq="2" place="above">down</add></subst> between the dusty trees,</l>
				<l n="2" rendition="#ti-1"><subst><del seq="1">Over the <gap extent="1 word" unit="chars" atLeast="7" /> broken</del><add seq="1" place="above">At this guant <del><gap extent="1-2 words" unit="chars" atLeast="4"/> <unclear cert="medium">woodâs haggard</unclear> <gap extent="1 word" unit="chars" atLeast="2"/></del></add> <add place="above">edge</add> of haggard wood,</l>
				<l n="3"><subst><del seq="1"><unclear cert="low">Loved</unclear> by</del><add seq="2" place="above"><del>Prayed to by</del></add><add seq="3" place="inline"><del>The women</del></add><add seq="4" place="above">Women</add></subst> with labour-loosened knees,</l>
				<l n="4" rendition="#ti-1"><subst><del seq="1">Find thee &amp; kneel &amp;</del><add seq="2" place="above">With gaunt backs bowed by servitude,</add></subst></l>
				<l n="5"> Stop, shift their loads, &amp; <subst><del seq="1"><gap extent="1 word" unit="chars" atLeast="4" />, <unclear cert="low">&amp;</unclear> <gap extent="1 word" unit="chars" atLeast="4" /></del><add seq="2" place="above"><unclear cert="low">have <!-- hum? --> their</unclear> prayer</add><add place="below" seq="3">pary, &amp; <del><unclear cert="low">pass</unclear> fare</l>
				<!-- paused. -->
				<l n="6"> Forth with souls easier for the prayer.</l>
			</lg>
			<lg>
				<l n="7"> The suns have branded black, the rains</l>
				<l n="8" rendition="#ti-1"> Striped grey this piteous God of theirs;</l>
				<l n="9"> The face is full of prayers and pains,</l>
				<l n="10" rendition="#ti-1"> To which they bring their pains and prayers;</l>
				<l n="11"> Lean limbs that shew the labouring bones,</l>
				<l n="12"> And ghastly mouth that gapes and groans.</l>
			</lg>
			<lg>
				<l n="13"> God of this grievous people, wrought</l>
				<l n="14" rendition="#ti-1"> After the likeness of their race,</l>
				<l n="15"> By faces like thine own besought,</l>
				<l n="16" rendition="#ti-1"> Thine own blind helpless eyeless face,</l>
				<l n="17"> I too, that have nor tongue nor knee</l>
				<l n="18"> For prayer, I have a word to thee.</l>
			</lg>
			<lg>
				<l n="19"> It was for this then, that thy speech</l>
				<l n="20" rendition="#ti-1"> Was blown about the world in flame</l>
				<l n="21"> And men's souls shot up out of reach</l>
